Higher than normal tides and strong rip currents will be experienced CAPE TOWN The National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) is urging bathers to be cautious, as the new moon spring tide peaks tomorrow.As a result, higher than normal tides and strong rip currents will be experienced.The spring tide will last until the 2 January.The NSRI'S Craig Lambinon says they are calling on beachgoers to be extra vigilant along the coast. The rip currents are certainly a concern at this time of the year because so many more people will be down at the beaches as we head into the New Year. (Edited by Neo Koza)